    "body": "So, regarding `msg.sender` and `constant`; if it's invoked via `eth_call`, the `msg.sender` is the coinbase or first account of the node executing the call (IIRC from when I looked into this earlier). The thing is, when `eth_call` is made, there's no actual _signed_ transaction being executed, so geth is forced to use something. And `coinbase` is most often a better choice than `0x00000..000`. \r\n\r\nI don't know what geth could do differently, so I'll close this. If it's not working as intended, or I've misinterpreted it, please open it again. ",
